I"&<p>Here is how I configured Anaconda and Pytorch on the Ubuntu 18.04 system
mentioned here <a href="http://phwl.org/2019/ubuntu-nvdia-19/">http://phwl.org/2019/ubuntu-nvdia-19/</a>.</p>

<ul>
  <li>Install Anaconda from <a href="https://www.anaconda.com/distribution">https://www.anaconda.com/distribution</a>
    <div class="highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>conda update -n base -c defaults conda
conda create --name dtw
conda activate dtw
conda install pytorch=0.4
</code></pre></div>    </div>
  </li>
</ul>

